Heterogeneous network flow is a function encoding: transfer, a classic form of intra-layer network flow, and coupling, a form of inter-layer flow establishing exogenous relationship between layers in the form of transformation. Unlike traditional network flow, the function satisfies both flow and mass conservation (Fig. 2e), due to Petri net correspondence. Formally, given a heterogeneous flow network \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
